description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you a proactive and enthusiastic Health Economist, Researcher or Scientist with experience in developing, reviewing and critiquing economic models that inform health technology assessments?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Reporting to the Principle Technical Adviser, the Senior Scientific Adviser will lead the Preliminary Independent Model Advice (PRIMA) service, providing early independent advice on economic models in development as part of submissions to programmes producing guidance at NICE.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;What you will bring to NICE:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;To be considered for this role, we are looking for:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;a postgraduate qualification in health economics and have a background in a life science, health policy or a quantitative field (e.g. statistics, biostatics, clinical trials or epidemiology).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;specialist knowledge of the principles of economic modelling and substantial experience in developing and critiquing such models developed in Excel or other specialist modelling software.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;a good understanding of the principles of evidence-based healthcare, critical appraisal and the interpretation and synthesis or healthcare research evidence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;a team player willing to provide expert technical and methodological input in to all aspects of the work of NICE Scientific Advice.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;an understanding of the social, political, economic and technical context within which the NICE operates and familiarity with its functions and programmes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder should be able to demonstrate the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;the ability to gather data, analyse, critique and synthesise complex information and prepare reports, briefing documents, presentations and guidance documents.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;good communication skills, demonstrating oral, written and presentation skills with a high degree of personal credibility, sensitivity and an ability to perform under pressure.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;the ability to establish effective working relationships within a multidisciplinary team, a range of professionals both within and outside the Institute, as well as with diverse stakeholders with limited experience of health economics and related fields.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;leadership skills including mentoring and line managing junior team members, the ability to work independently and produce work of high quality to tight deadlines.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;proven ability to contribute to business development, represent the Programme and Institute at external events, conferences and educational activities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Why NICE:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Here at NICE we are passionate and proud of the work we do and the impact we make.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We can offer you a great place to work with good benefits, flexible working and a supportive, friendly and inclusive environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have an academic culture committed to producing high quality work and we take collective responsibility.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;NICE Scientific Advice Programme:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;NICE Scientific Advice provides fee-for-service advice to developers of pharmaceuticals, medical technologies and diagnostics. The advice aims to optimise the evidence available to inform any future NICE guidance of the health technologies. The advice offered draws on experience within the Institute, working in partnership with external experts, patient representatives, regulators, HTA bodies, the NHS and academia.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For an informal discussion please contact Eli Gajraj, Principle Technical Adviser (elangovan.gajraj@nice.org.uk).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
